A year ago I was close to hanging them up and getting into coaching. During that time of darkness and struggle, God used many people in my life to help me battle with my inner demons caused by this tough sport. 

There are three people in particular who I want to thank. I want to thank my Lord and Savior Jesus Christ for using my pain for good. Using my losses in this sport for something greater. For giving me life and the opportunity to use this amazing sport to honor Him, win or lose.

I want to thank my wife Moriah for always bELIeving in me and supporting me throughout my wrestling career. Every day she tells me I will reach my goal of becoming an Olympic Champion. She has and will always be my number 1.

I want to now thank my mentor and the greatest wrestling coach there is, Tom Brands. Tom is the most loyal, supportive and genuine person you will ever meet. He was one of the reasons I’m still competing today. I know it’s ultimately my decision to compete but it’s the endless conversations with him that allowed me to grow and chase that goal. Love you Tom.

Thank you everyone for your love and support. I’m having a blast. ✝️
